<|startoftext|>This was my first time there, it was really good, the waitress was great, she gave us a full set massage. The restaurant has some great wine and food, but they only offer a small selection of alcohol to choose from. We enjoyed the beer as well. It was around 23-25$\nThis was the perfect spot to grab before heading out to the strip. The food was great, I got a shrimp cocktail and the crab cakes were also delicious :)<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>So a little out front of the store... I would say I'd give it one star if I could. I had the fried shrimp and scallop appetizer, and it was dry and unappealing. I'll say it up- top... this was the best dinner I've EVER had at a Lasik Experience! The price was amazing and I love that this place offers a large selection of glasses. They even offer to take-away and bring-up your glasses if you want. I had to wait quite a bit for my service, so I gave some good tips to the waiter. I ordered a few sides, but the shrimp and the scallop appetizer were my highlights. I'm not a fan of chicken, and this side was tasty, but I will have to say that it works well on fried shrimp. I loved it.\n\nMy one point was the fact that they do not offer unlimited complimentary refills. Which is a huge plus with my family. Plus it is just expensive enough. And, as I've said before, the glasses are large enough that I'll leave with 10 glasses of my own.\n\nHowever, if I am ever in the area, I'd definitely eat here again.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>This little spot makes me feel as if I are in Chinatown. I always wanted to come here but didn't know how to get in. I wanted to try some of their sandwiches, and the little red box that they had that just kept coming up was really a good size. I got a little order of hot and sour soup, which was a bit different, however it was tasty and filling! I usually hate the way they make their sandwiches because their ingredients aren't all fresh, but after I ordered lunch this time, the ingredients were fresh! The salad that came was also fresh! My server was great!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>The food was pretty good overall. I've been to a lot of Mexican places in my life. This place was very good, but the place definitely took a turn. I was seated right away and sat at the bar. I had the meat burrito and beans as an appetizer and the burrito itself was yummy. For my entree, I opted for the ceviche and the beef shortribs were delicious at least for lunch. The portion I opted for was small and not the largest or anything like that but the food was still not bad<|endoftext|>
